        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 12:17PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 1217 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles south of Gascon, or 13 miles southwest of Mora, moving
northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tierra Monte, Gascon, Ledoux, Morphy Lake State Park, Sapello,
Rociada, South Carmen and Manuelitas.

This includes the following highways...
State Road 94 between Mile Markers 1 and 17.
State Road 518 between Mile Markers 12 and 17.
State Road 276 between Mile Markers 0 and 5.
State Road 266 between Mile Markers 0 and 6.
State Road 105 between Mile Markers 0 and 9.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
